00:00:13.110 --> 00:00:17.700
A decimal fraction is a fraction
where the denominator is a power

00:00:17.700 --> 00:00:21.870
of 10, like 1,000, 1000, et cetera.

00:00:22.290 --> 00:00:27.060
Instead of writing the denominator,
we use a decimal point.to

00:00:27.060 --> 00:00:28.710
represent the fractional part.

00:00:29.120 --> 00:00:32.720
The digits to the right of the
decimal part represent parts of

00:00:32.720 --> 00:00:34.910
a whole based on powers of 10.

00:00:35.090 --> 00:00:39.110
For example, 0.5 represents five by 10.

00:00:39.290 --> 00:00:47.480
0.25 represents 25 by a hundred and
0.125 represents 1 25 by thousand.

00:00:47.810 --> 00:00:52.640
It's like slicing a cake
into 1,000 or 1000 pieces.

00:00:53.150 --> 00:00:56.480
