00:01:04.640 --> 00:01:08.390
Then the whole number part, the
digits to the left of the decimal

00:01:08.390 --> 00:01:10.580
point, representing complete units.

00:01:11.080 --> 00:01:15.040
And the fractional part, the digits
to the right of the decimal part,

00:01:15.190 --> 00:01:17.020
representing parts of a whole.

00:01:17.440 --> 00:01:21.640
Each digit in a decimal number
has a specific place value to

00:01:21.640 --> 00:01:23.080
the right of the decimal point.

00:01:23.200 --> 00:01:28.750
The places are tens, one by 10
hundreds, one by hundred thousands,

00:01:28.810 --> 00:01:31.090
one by thousand and so on.

00:01:31.414 --> 00:01:35.585
